Package: fightr
Type: Package
Title: Analyze Fight Probabilities and Props via Statistical Frameworks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Benjamin",
             family = "Smith",
             role = c("aut", "cre"),
             email = "benyamin.smith@mail.utoronto.ca",
             comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0007-2206-0177"))
  )
Description: Provides a statistical framework for modeling combat sports 
    matchups and estimating latent fighter ability parameters. Predicts the 
    probability of a win and the specific method of victory using historical 
    bout data and biometric differentials. Implements multiple maximum 
    likelihood estimation approaches, including multinomial logistic regression 
    and degree-two pairwise comparison network models (Bradley-Terry and 
    Thurstone-Mosteller). To ensure analytical relevance in a continuously 
    updating sport, the package utilizes a CRAN-compliant dynamic caching 
    architecture to seamlessly retrieve and update the latest athlete profiles, 
    performance metrics, and fight outcomes.
